{
  "texts": [
    "It adjusts the LoRA rank and redistributes the SVD components of the global LoRA weights based on resource constraints.",
    "Similarly, HETLORA [105] assigns different ranks for different clients.",
    "However, it performs weighted aggregation according to the sparsity of the updates from different clients, balancing update information better than simple aggregation.",
    "Model heterogeneityModel heterogeneity indicates differences in model structures among clients.",
    "In traditional federated learning, clients use local models with the same architecture, allowing their parameters to be aggregated into a global model on the server."
  ]
}